{"title_page": "MacPaw", "text_new": "{{Advert|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name                  = MacPaw\n| logo                  = \n| type                  = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| founder               = Oleksandr Kosovan\n| foundation            = 2008; 11 years ago\n| location              = [[Kyiv, Ukraine]]\n| area_served           = Worldwide\n| key_people            = Oleksandr Kosovan (CEO)\n| industry              = {{flatlist|\n*[[Information Technology]]\n*[[Software]]\n}}\n| products              = {{flatlist|\n\n*[[Setapp]]\n*[[The Unarchiver]]\n*Gemini 2\n*[[CleanMyMac]]\n}}\n| revenue               =\n| operating_income      =\n| net_income            =\n| assets                =\n| equity                =\n| num_employees         = 200\n| parent                = \n| homepage              = {{URL|https://macpaw.com/}}           \n}}\n\n'''MacPaw''' is a Ukrainian software company with a headquarters in [[Kyiv]], [[Ukraine]] that develops and distributes software for [[macOS]] and [[iOS]]. Its products include [[CleanMyMac]], [[Setapp]], Gemini Photos and more. The company was founded in 2008. MacPaw's revenue was $23 million in 2018.<ref name=\"ukraine-is-the-best\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbestechcouncil/2018/10/16/ukraine-is-the-best-kept-secret-in-californias-startup-scene/#7a23edf87ebc \n| title = Ukraine Is The Best Kept Secret In California's Startup Scene \n| work = [[forbes.com]] \n| date = 2018-10-16 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}\n</ref> The company claims that one in five Macs worldwide run an app by MacPaw, as of June 2019.<ref name=\"why-apple-evangelist\"/>\n\n== History == \nMacPaw was founded by Oleksandr Kosovan, then a student at [[Kyiv Polytechnic Institute]]. The company's first app was [[CleanMyMac]] and made $4,000<ref name=\"why-apple-evangelist\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/335300 \n| title = Why Apple Evangelist Oleksandr Kosovan Is Competing With His Favorite Company \n| work = [[entrepreneur.com]] \n| date = 2019-06-18 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}\n</ref> in its first month. Kosovan wrote the code himself. The company was [[bootstrapped]]. Kosovan called the company, MacPaw, after Apple's operating systems, which were named after big cats like Cheetah and Tiger at the time.<ref name=\"macpaw-software-for\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://www.kyivpost.com/article/content/ukraines-it-edge/macpaw-software-for-cleaning-macs-earns-worldwide-affection-382783.html \n| title = MacPaw software for cleaning Macs earns worldwide affection \n| work = [[kyivpost.com]] \n| date = 2015-03-06 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}\n</ref>\n\nMacPaw launched [[Setapp]], a [[subscription service]] for apps, in January 2017.<ref name=\"subscription-service-for\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://techcrunch.com/2018/01/24/mac-app-subscription-service-setapp-has-15000-subscribers-a-year-after-its-launch/ \n| title = Subscription service for Mac apps Setapp has 15,000 subscribers a year after its launch \n| work = [[techcrunch.com]] \n| date = 2018-01-24 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}</ref><ref name=\"macpaw-setapp-service\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://www.macworld.com/article/3161490/macpaws-setapp-service-offers-a-suite-of-mac-software-for-a-monthly-fee.html \n| title = MacPaw's Setapp service offers a suite of Mac software for a monthly fee \n| work = [[macworld.com]] \n| date = 2017-01-25 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}</ref> The company merged software development and distribution tool DevMate into Paddle's e-commerce platform in May 2017.<ref name=\"london-based-e-commerce\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://startups.co.uk/paddle-merges-with-devmate/ \n| title = London-based e-commerce firm Paddle merges with software company DevMate \n| work = [[startups.co.uk]] \n| date = 2017-05-24 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}</ref><ref name=\"paddle-the-software\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://techcrunch.com/2017/12/14/paddle-raises-12-5m/ \n| title = Paddle, the software sales platform founded by a Thiel Fellow, raises $12.5M  \n| work = [[techcrunch.com]] \n| date = 2017-12-14 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}</ref> MacPaw acquired [[The Unarchiver]] in July 2017<ref name=\"macpaw-acquires-the\">{{cite news \n| url = https://9to5mac.com/2017/07/27/macpaw-acquires-the-unarchiver-mac-app/ \n| title = MacPaw acquires The Unarchiver Mac app, will keep it updated & free \n| work = 9to5mac.com \n| date = 2017-07-27 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}</ref><ref name=\"why-apple-evangelist\" />  and Wallpaper Wizard in August 2017.<ref name=\"wallpaper-wizard-2-makes\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://www.appleworld.today/blog/2017/8/29/wallpaper-wizard-2-makes-it-easy-to-use-hd-wallpapers-on-your-mac \n| title = Wallpaper Wizard 2 makes it easy to use HD wallpapers on your Mac \n| work = appleworld.today \n| date = 2017-08-29 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}</ref>\n\nMacPaw publishes an annual survey of developers on the Mac App Store.<ref name=\"mac-app-store-continues\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://venturebeat.com/2018/10/15/mac-app-store-continues-to-bleed-developers-over-analytics-and-trials/ \n| title = Mac App Store continues to bleed developers over analytics and trials \n| work = [[venturebeat.com]] \n| date = 2018-10-15 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}</ref><ref name=\"the-mac-app-store\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://thenextweb.com/apple/2017/06/15/the-mac-app-store-is-now-slightly-less-hated-by-mac-developers/ \n| title = The Mac App Store is now slightly less hated by developers \n| work = [[thenextweb.com]] \n| date = 2017-06-16 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}</ref>\n\nMacPaw houses one of the largest [[vintage]] collections of working Apple computers and devices in the world.<ref name=\"why-apple-evangelist\" /><ref name=\"If-employees-break\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://www.businessinsider.com/macpaw-campus-photo-tour-apple-museum-2018-4\n| title = This Ukrainian startup has its own Apple museum filled with rare gadgets \u2014 and we got a private tour\n| work = [[businessinsider.com]] \n| date =  2018-04-04\n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}</ref> The collection began when Kosovan purchased the Mac Museum<ref name=\"ukraine-may-soon\">{{cite news \n| url = https://venturebeat.com/2017/12/29/ukraine-may-soon-have-worlds-largest-apple-museum-thanks-to-macpaw-founders-obsession/ \n| title = Ukraine may soon have world's largest Apple museum, thanks to MacPaw founder's obsession \n| work = [[venturebeat.com]] \n| date = 2017-12-29  \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}</ref> from [[Tekserve]].<ref name=\"multiport-hub-is\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://www.cultofmac.com/480893/tekserves-apple-artifacts-wind-ukrainian-museum/ \n| title = Tekserve's Apple artifacts wind up in Ukrainian museum\n| work = cultofmac.com \n| date = 2017-05-11 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}</ref>\n\n== Awards & Achievements ==\nMacPaw won a [[Red Dot design award]] in 2017 for Gemini 2 in the Communication Design category.<ref name=\"wins-red-dot-award-mac-gemini\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://www.cultofmac.com/511419/indie-developer-wins-red-dot-award-mac-gemini/ \n| title = Indie developer wins prestigious Red Dot design award for Mac app \n| work = cultofmac.com \n| date = 2017-11-01 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}</ref> Setapp won a [[Product Hunt]] Golden Kitty Award for Consumer Product of the Year in January 2018.<ref name=\"golden-kitty-awards-winners\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://blog.producthunt.com/golden-kitty-awards-winners-7c2628e5f429 \n| title = Golden Kitty Awards Winners \n| work = blog.producthunt.com \n| date = 2018-01-29 \n| accessdate = 2019-10-03 }}</ref> Setapp was named one of the most innovative companies<ref name=\"europe\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://www.fastcompany.com/most-innovative-companies/2019/sectors/europe \n| title = The World's Most Innovative Companies 2019: Europe Honorees \n| work = [[fastcompany.com]] }}</ref> in Europe in 2019 by [[Fast Company]] and won the 2019 SaaS Award for Best SaaS Product for Productivity (non-US).<ref name=\"2019-saas-shortlist\">{{cite news \n| url = https://www.cloud-awards.com/2019-saas-shortlist/ \n| title = 2019 SaaS Winners Cloud Computing & SaaS Awards \n| work = cloud-awards.com }}\n</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Technology companies established in 2008]]\n[[Category:Development software companies]]\n[[Category:Software companies of Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Organizations based in Kiev]]\n", "text_old": "{{Advert|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name                  = MacPaw\n| logo                  = \n| type                  = [[Privately held company|Private]]\n| founder               = Oleksandr Kosovan\n| foundation            = 2008; 11 years ago\n| location              = [[Kyiv, Ukraine]]\n| area_served           = Worldwide\n| key_people            = Oleksandr Kosovan (CEO)\n| industry              = {{flatlist|\n*[[Information Technology]]\n*[[Software]]\n}}\n| products              = {{flatlist|\n\n*[[Setapp]]\n*[[The Unarchiver]]\n*Gemini 2\n*CleanMyMac\n}}\n| revenue               =\n| operating_income      =\n| net_income            =\n| assets                =\n| equity                =\n| num_employees         = 200\n| parent                = \n| homepage              = {{URL|https://macpaw.com/}}           \n}}\n\n'''MacPaw''' is a Ukrainian software company with a headquarters in [[Kyiv]], [[Ukraine]] that develops and distributes software for [[macOS]] and [[iOS]]. Its products include CleanMyMac, [[Setapp]], Gemini Photos and more. The company was founded in 2008. MacPaw's revenue was $23 million in 2018.<ref name=\"ukraine-is-the-best\">\n{{cite news \n| url = https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbestechcouncil/2018/10/16/ukraine-is-the-best-kept-secret-in-californias-startup-scene/#7a23edf87ebc \n| title = Ukraine Is The Best Kept Secret In California's Startup Scene \n| work = [[forbes.com]] \n| date = 2018-